                {
                    "_comment": "Inertial impaction term before the density correction (slinn_collection_efficiency, src line 347): safe_ratio*sqrt(safe_ratio) = safe_ratio^(3/2). Upstream wraps this in ifelse(St-S* ≤ 0, 0, safe_ratio*sqrt(safe_ratio)) so the term is zero when St ≤ S* (impaction requires sufficient inertia; Seinfeld & Pandis p. 950); the ifelse is omitted because safe_ratio = max(0, St-S*)/(max(0, St-S*) + 2/3) is already exactly 0 when St-S* ≤ 0, so both ifelse branches are bit-identical.",
